TEST 4 — Sparse Spiking Dynamics
Directory: experiments/04-sparse-spiking
Build a spiking neural network experiment in Python. This is cognitive architecture research
WHAT TO BUILD:
A leaky integrate-and-fire spiking neural network with N=1000 neurons. Implement from scratch
Neuron model:
dV/dt = -V/τ + I_input + I_recurrent
Where:
- V is membrane potential (reset to 0 after firing)
- τ = 20ms time constant
- Neuron fires when V > threshold (threshold = 1.0)
- After firing: V = 0, absolute refractory period = 2ms
Network structure:
- 80% excitatory neurons, 20% inhibitory (Dale's law)
- Sparse random connectivity: each neuron connects to 5% of others
- Excitatory weights: positive, drawn from exponential distribution
- Inhibitory weights: negative, 4x stronger than excitatory (balance)
- No learning rule in this experiment — fixed weights
Input:
- Inject current pulses to random 10% of neurons at irregular intervals
- Three input patterns: Pattern A, B, C — each activates a different 10% subset
- Present each pattern 20 times in random order
